main event: On September 20, 1966, an observer in Gwinner, North Dakota reported seeing an unidentified object with a glass bubble and lighted area traveling northwest while emitting a humming sound.
interesting points: The object left depressions in the ground indicative of disturbance, resembling impressions made by a bowling ball,The UFO was observed moving slowly and was described as typical-shaped with a glass bubble,Several witnesses reported the same sighting around the same timeframe,One witness reported that the weather conditions were good with visibility,The incident coincided with a power outage in the area affecting electric service for about four hours.
sighted object: Unidentified flying object with a glass bubble on top
witness description: A young observer, estimated age 12, whose reliability was considered excellent for his age.
